parameters.name: Br
parameters.description: Radial (along the Jupiter to spacecraft line) magnetic field component, positive away from Jupiter.

parameters.name: Btheta
parameters.description: Southward field component, System III [1965] coordinates.

parameters.name: Bphi
parameters.description: Corotational field component, System III [1965] coordinates.

parameters.name: B-field Magnitude
parameters.description: Magnitude of the average B-field components.

parameters.name: Range
parameters.description: Range of the spacecraft from the Jupiter center of mass in units of Jupiter radii where 1 Rj = 71492 km.

parameters.name: Latitude
parameters.description: Planetographic latitude of the spacecraft in degrees.

parameters.name: Longitude
parameters.description: Planetographic east longitude of the spacecraft in degrees.

parameters.name: Local Time
parameters.description: Angle between the observer's (spacecraft) sub-Jupiter meridian and the anti-sunward meridian, measured in the Jovian equatorial plane in the direction of planetary rotation. The local hour angle is converted to a decimal hour (one hour equal to fifteen degrees longitude). The sun meridian is defined to be noon (12.000), with midnight (0.000) opposite it. Dawn (6.000) and dusk (18.000) are where the sun rises and sets according to the planet's rotation.
